{{Infobox football biography | name = Lys Mousset | image = | fullname = Lys Émilien Mousset<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.thefa.com/-/media/files/thefaportal/governance-docs/registrations/player-registration---july-2016.ashx |title=List of Players under Written Contract Registered Between 01/07/2016 and 31/07/2016 |publisher=The Football Association |format=PDF |page=23 |accessdate=2 February 2019}}</ref> | birth_date = {{birth date and age|1996|02|08|df=y}} | birth_place = [[Montivilliers]], France | height = 1.84 m | position = [[Forward (association football)|Forward]] | currentclub = [[A.F.C. Bournemouth|AFC Bournemouth]] | clubnumber = 9 | youthyears1 = 2003–2004 | youthclubs1 = Soquence Graville | youthyears2 = 2004–2006 | youthclubs2 = Havre Caucriauville | youthyears3 = 2006–2012 | youthclubs3 = [[Le Havre AC|Le Havre]] | years1 = 2012–2015 | clubs1 = [[Le Havre AC|Le Havre II]] | caps1 = 57 | goals1 = 14 | years2 = 2014–2016 | clubs2 = [[Le Havre AC|Le Havre]] | caps2 = 34 | goals2 = 14 | years3 = 2016– | clubs3 = [[A.F.C. Bournemouth|AFC Bournemouth]] | caps3 = 53 | goals3 = 3 | nationalyears1 = 2015–2016 | nationalteam1 = [[France national under-20 football team|France U20]] | nationalcaps1 = 8 | nationalgoals1 = 1 | nationalyears2 = 2017– | nationalteam2 = [[France national under-21 football team|France U21]] | nationalcaps2 = 8 | nationalgoals2 = 5 | club-update = 10:22, 28 February 2019 (UTC) | nationalteam-update = 13 November 2017 }} '''Lys Émilien Mousset''' (born 8 February 1996) is a French footballer who currently plays for [[A.F.C. Bournemouth|AFC Bournemouth]] in the [[Premier League]]. He is a [[France national under-21 football team|France U21]] international.
==Career== ===Le Havre=== He joined [[Le Havre AC|Le Havre]] academy in 2006 after playing for local clubs Soquence Graville and Havre Caucriauville. He graduated to [[Le Havre AC|Le Havre II]] where he impressed scoring 14 goals before making his debut for [[Le Havre AC|Le Havre]] first team, again scoring 14 goals in 34 games.
===AFC Bournemouth=== On 30 June 2016, Mousset joined [[A.F.C. Bournemouth|AFC Bournemouth]] from [[Le Havre AC|Le Havre]] for a €7.3 million transfer fee.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://twitter.com/HAC_Foot/status/748514035696570368|title=HAC Football on Twitter|date=30 June 2016|website=twitter.com/HAC_Foot|publisher=HAC Football (Le Havre)|language=French|access-date=30 June 2016}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.skysports.com/football/news/11743/10329407/bournemouth-complete-transfer-of-lys-mousset-from-le-havre|title=Bournemouth complete transfer of Lys Mousset from Le Havre|last=Lustig|first=Nick|date=30 June 2016|website=www.skysports.com|publisher=Sky Sports|access-date=30 June 2016}}</ref> He scored his first goal for Bournemouth in an [[FA Cup]] tie against [[Wigan Athletic]] on 6 January 2018.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/42519385|title=Bournemouth 2-2 Wigan |publisher=[[BBC]] |date=6 January 2018 |accessdate=7 January 2018}}</ref>
==International career== Mousset was born in France to a Senegalese father and a French mother, and is eligible for both countries.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://seneprolongations.com/talent-cache-lys-mendy-le-meconnu-des-senegalais-de-premier-league-8989|title=Talent Caché : Lys Mendy, le méconnu des sénégalais de Premier League !|publisher=}}</ref> He made his [[France national under-20 football team|France U20]] debut in 2015.
